# kube-prometheus-stack Upgrade Path
## `61.2.0` → `82.15.1` — CVE-2024-41110 Remediation
 
> **Context:** This upgrade path remediates **CVE-2024-41110** (Critical — Docker authorization bypass) affecting `github.com/docker/docker` bundled in Prometheus images `v2.44.0` and `v2.46.0`.  
> Performed in **4 controlled hops** to avoid breaking changes across CRD boundaries.
 
---
 
## 📋 Upgrade Overview Table
 
| Phase | From | To | Prometheus | Prom-Operator | CVE Status | Breaking Changes |
|-------|------|----|------------|---------------|------------|-----------------|
| **Phase 1** | `61.2.0` | `62.6.0` | `v2.44/46` | `v0.75.x` | ❌ Still Vulnerable | None expected |
| **Phase 2** | `62.6.0` | `65.8.1` | `v2.54.1` | `v0.77.1` | ⚠️ Partially Mitigated | Minor: kubeScheduler rules split |
| **Phase 3** | `65.8.1` | `68.8.0` | `v2.54.x` | `v0.78.x` | ⚠️ Partially Mitigated | CRD auto-upgrade job available |
| **Phase 4** | `68.8.0` | `82.15.1` | `v3.x` | `v0.89.0` | ✅ **FIXED** | Prometheus v2→v3 config flags |
 
