## 🚀 Phase-by-Phase Upgrade Instructions
 
### Pre-flight Checklist (Run Before Every Phase)
 
```bash
# 1. Backup current Helm values
helm get values prometheus -n monitoring > values-backup-$(date +%F).yaml
 
# 2. Check current deployed chart version
helm list -n monitoring
 
# 3. Preview changes before applying
helm diff upgrade prometheus prometheus-community/kube-prometheus-stack \
  --version <TARGET_VERSION> \
  --reuse-values \
  --namespace monitoring
```
 
---
 
### Phase 1 — `61.2.0` → `62.6.0`
 
**What changes:** Minor CRD additions, no API renames. Safe warm-up hop.
 
```bash
# Step 1: Update repo
helm repo update
 
# Step 2: Update CRDs (Operator v0.75.0)
for crd in alertmanagerconfigs alertmanagers podmonitors probes prometheusagents \
           prometheuses prometheusrules scrapeconfigs servicemonitors thanosrulers; do
  kubectl apply --server-side -f \
    https://raw.githubusercontent.com/prometheus-operator/prometheus-operator/v0.75.0/example/prometheus-operator-crd/monitoring.coreos.com_${crd}.yaml
done
 
# Step 3: Dry-run
helm upgrade prometheus prometheus-community/kube-prometheus-stack \
  --namespace monitoring \
  --version 62.6.0 \
  --reuse-values --dry-run
 
# Step 4: Apply
helm upgrade prometheus prometheus-community/kube-prometheus-stack \
  --namespace monitoring \
  --version 62.6.0 \
  --reuse-values
 
# Step 5: Verify
kubectl get pods -n monitoring
kubectl get prometheus -n monitoring
```
 
**✅ Post-check:** All pods `Running`, Prometheus UI accessible.
 
---
 
### Phase 2 — `62.6.0` → `65.8.1`
 
**What changes:** Prometheus `v2.53 → v2.54.1`, Operator `v0.75 → v0.77.1`.  
 
> ⚠️ **Breaking:** `defaultRules.rules.kubeScheduler` is split into  
> `defaultRules.rules.kubeSchedulerAlerting` and `defaultRules.rules.kubeSchedulerRecording`.  
> Update your `values.yaml` if you override `kubeScheduler` rules.
 
```bash
# Step 1: Update values.yaml if needed
# OLD:  defaultRules.rules.kubeScheduler: true
# NEW:  defaultRules.rules.kubeSchedulerAlerting: true
#       defaultRules.rules.kubeSchedulerRecording: true
 
# Step 2: Update CRDs (Operator v0.77.0)
for crd in alertmanagerconfigs alertmanagers podmonitors probes prometheusagents \
           prometheuses prometheusrules scrapeconfigs servicemonitors thanosrulers; do
  kubectl apply --server-side -f \
    https://raw.githubusercontent.com/prometheus-operator/prometheus-operator/v0.77.0/example/prometheus-operator-crd/monitoring.coreos.com_${crd}.yaml
done
 
# Step 3: Dry-run
helm upgrade prometheus prometheus-community/kube-prometheus-stack \
  --namespace monitoring \
  --version 65.8.1 \
  --reuse-values --dry-run
 
# Step 4: Apply
helm upgrade prometheus prometheus-community/kube-prometheus-stack \
  --namespace monitoring \
  --version 65.8.1 \
  --reuse-values
 
# Step 5: Verify
kubectl get pods -n monitoring
kubectl get prometheus -n monitoring
```
 
**✅ Post-check:** Confirm ServiceMonitor discovery intact, dashboards loading.
 
---
 
### Phase 3 — `65.8.1` → `68.8.0`
 
**What changes:** Operator `v0.77 → v0.78`, CRD auto-upgrade job introduced.
 
> ℹ️ From `68.4.0` onwards, you can enable automatic CRD upgrades via:
> ```yaml
> crds:
>   upgradeJob:
>     enabled: true
> ```
 

